This paper deals with the problem of spectral graph sparsification, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science and numerical analysis. The algorithmic aspect of the problem suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of spectral methods and the Laplacian matrix suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the numerical analysis aspect of the problem suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NA, cs.CG, and cs.LG, in that order.
